    <p>When you arrive in Italy as an expat, foreigner, or tourist, one of the first things you'll need to learn is how to identify a legitimate farmacia. The green cross, known locally as the "croce verde," is the official symbol that distinguishes licensed pharmacies throughout Italy. This green illuminated cross has been the standard pharmacy identifier in Italy for decades and is regulated by regional health authorities.</p>
