    <p>Antihistamines, medications blocking histamine causing allergic symptoms, are the primary allergy treatment. Italian farmacie stock numerous antihistamine options in oral, nasal spray, and eye drop forms. Cetirizine (marketed as Pollergin and other brand names in Italy) is a popular non-drowsy antihistamine available without prescription, costing €5-€12 for packages containing 10-30 tablets.</p>
