    <p>Italy's pediatric healthcare through the SSN provides comprehensive care for children from birth through age 14. Selecting a pediatrician establishes ongoing healthcare relationships and continuity of care. Italian pharmacies stock comprehensive pediatric medications and products addressing common childhood health concerns. Infant nutrition products and breastfeeding support are readily available. Common childhood illnesses are managed through supportive care and over-the-counter medications. Specialized products for skin conditions, allergies, and growth support address specific children's needs. Building a home first-aid kit with pediatric medications prevents urgent pharmacy visits for minor concerns. Understanding Italian pediatric healthcare system empowers expat parents to manage their children's health confidently.</p>

