    <p>Non-residents or those without SSN registration pay standardized rates for emergency room visits. Costs vary by region and complexity: simple evaluation might cost €50-150, while extensive testing and treatment cost €200-500. Major procedures or hospitalization incur higher costs, though these are still reasonable compared to other developed countries. Travel insurance covering medical care is recommended for visitors and those not yet registered with the SSN. Always inform the emergency room about your insurance status upon arrival.</p>

