    <p>Comfort items are secondary to emergency treatment but may be helpful during waits: a sweater for temperature control, phone chargers for extended stays, and entertainment for waiting areas. Someone accompanying you (family member, friend) provides emotional support and can help communicate with staff if language barriers exist. Children may benefit from comfort items like stuffed animals or blankets, though emergency room staff are trained supporting pediatric patients.</p>

