    <p>If admitted, you're transferred to an appropriate hospital ward (medical, surgical, cardiac care, etc.). Hospital admissions in Italy typically result from serious conditions, significant injuries, or need for procedures. Hospital stays are usually brief by international standards—2-5 days for many conditions. If admitted, emergency room physicians will explain your condition and treatment plan. Family members are typically allowed to stay with patients, though visiting hours may apply.</p>

